The paper proposes a new dynamic filtering strategy for ConvNets that improves object detection, semantic segmentation, and flow estimation. These tasks are all related to computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper introduces an attention mechanism and residual learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the efficient use of parameters, which could be related to neural network optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia sub-category (cs.MM).
